data.title: HHTpywrapper: Python Wrapper for Hilbert–Huang Transform MATLAB Package
data.name: HHTpywrapper
data.description: Python Wrapper for Hilbert–Huang Transform MATLAB Package

evidence: README install command: "$ pip install -r requirements.txt"

"HHTpywrapper instantaneously tracks frequency and amplitude variations of a signal generated by non-stationary and nonlinear processes... It uses Python as an interface to call the Hilbert–Huang Transform (HHT) MATLAB package" (domain-specific analysis tool).

"This is the root directory of the package, including the directory of HHT MATLAB package and the Python API for calling the MATLAB package (eemd.py and hsa.py)." (Python API/package intended to be imported).
